</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-34">As only one coordinate is involved, it is imperative that COM lies on the line joining two particles. It can also be seen that center of mass lies in between the masses on the line connecting two particles. There are two additional simplified cases for two particles system as :
</para>
<para id="element-35">
<term>(i)</term> Origin of coordinate coincides with position of one of the particles :
</para>
<para id="element-36">
The expression of COM is simplified when position of one of the particles is the origin. For two particles system,  
