</para>
<para id="element-996">Note that the term in the numerator of the expression is nothing but the product of the mass of particle like small volumetric element and its distance from the origin along the axis. Evidently, this terms when integrated is equal to sum of all such products of mass elements constituting the rigid body.</para><para id="element-56">Evaluation of above integrals is simplified, if the density of the rigid body is uniform. In that case,
</para>
